Development Environment Setup Instructions
==========================================

Vyperlink is implemented in Python, and utilises a number of
libraries. The following sections describe one possible way of setting
up a working environment for Vyperlink.

This assumes a basic Ubuntu 12.04 (LTS) setup to begin with.


Python/Virtualenv setup
-----------------------
  ...as documented on http://www.virtualenv.org/en/latest/

    sudo apt-get install python-pip python-virtualenv

  In .../virtualenvs:

    virtualenv vyperenv
    source vyperenv/bin/activate


Other (Ubuntu) Packages
-----------------------

  sudo apt-get install mongodb build-essential python-dev
    (the latter two required by pip install mongoengine)



Python required packages
------------------------

Frameworks, interface layers, etc.:
  pip install flask flask-debugtoolbar mongoengine markdown

//  pip install flask-mongoengine

Not strictly necessary, but very useful:
  pip install ipython
